		<div>That is not a nude poster, that is a gaming chick!!<br />
<br />
The 21 inch CRT has since been replaced by another 17inch lcd.<br />
I find having one main (in the middle) and the others just support makes having keyboard and mouse on all of them not a big thing.  Hot keys and eqcompanion make it transparent.  Eqcompanion uses voice output to tell me when my snare hits/gets resisted, fizzles, other resists, slows land or dont land, etc.  So I seldom have to watch the other screens when I am doing camping kinda of stuff.   When I 3 box'd ldons (I just park the chanter at zi for buffs), the other 2 are on /follow.  I tried the gamepad thing, but found properly set up hotkeys and practice made them not necessary.  I now mostly just 2 box, druid and beast in wos and instances.  Just use the other 2 for buffing before heading out.<br />
<br />
showeq??  No no no!  That is, uh, that is..   that is my mapquest of Chicago!! <br />
