	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>If you don't feel the "need" to have 3+ monitors my setup is pretty simple.<br />
<br />
It is just a rectangular desk, you know the type, pretty standard really.  I have a keyboard drawer / shelf and just above that I've got enough room to put another keyboard so the keyboards are just above/below each other.  Mice are both off to the right of the keyboards, my two 21inch CRTs are next to each other just behind the keyboard on the top shelf, with the KVM switch under my primary monitor. <br />
<br />
Pretty basic setup really, nothing like those pictures posted above <img src="http://thedruidsgrove.org/forums/images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Stick Out Tongue" class="inlineimg" />.<br />
<br />
I also use a pretty cheap "helper" tool that GREATLY minimizes my need to even look at or even use the non-main keyboard or mouse.  Toss me an e-mail if you like and I'll let you know what it is.  <br />
<a href="mailto:clakareq@hotmail.com">clakareq@hotmail.com</a></div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
